58. curam . . . cohortis: the young man expects to repair his shattered fortunes in the public career open to him as a knight (eques). The regu· lar introduction to the equestrian cursus honorum, which included many very important functions (procurator, praefectus), was a period of mili- tary service as (1) praefectus cohortis sociorum, (2) tribunus leyionis, and (3) praefectus alae, usually in this order, though Claudius attempted to change it (Suet. 25).
